cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with codes over poset metrics, which are closely related to information theory and coding theory, hence the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses weight enumerators, which are a fundamental tool in coding theory and combinatorics, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely category. The paper also deals with MacWilliams identities, which are a well-known tool in coding theory, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with linear codes over Frobenius commutative rings, which is a topic in algebraic coding theory, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
